## Task
Implement review creation, editing, and deletion with enforcement of one review per user per place.

## One Review Per Place Policy
Users don't create new reviews for a place they've already reviewed - they EDIT.

```typescript
// convex/reviews.ts
export const upsertReview = mutation({
  args: {
    placeKey: v.string(),
    rating: v.number(),
    text: v.optional(v.string()),
    dishesTried: v.optional(v.array(v.string())),
    // ...
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const userId = await requireAuth(ctx);

    const existing = await ctx.db
      .query('reviews')
      .withIndex('by_user_place', (q) =>
        q.eq('userId', userId).eq('placeKey', args.placeKey)
      )
      .unique();

    if (existing) {
      // Update existing review
      await recordEditHistory(ctx, existing._id, args);
      return ctx.db.patch(existing._id, {
        ...args,
        updatedAt: Date.now(),
      });
    } else {
      // Create new review
      return ctx.db.insert('reviews', {
        userId,
        ...args,
        helpfulCount: 0,
        createdAt: Date.now(),
      });
    }
  },
});
```

## Review Structure
```typescript
{
  userId: Id<'users'>,
  placeKey: string,
  rating: number,          // 1-5
  text: string,            // 10-2000 chars
  dishesTried: string[],   // What they ordered
  pricePaidBucketMad: string, // '<30' | '30-70' | '70-150' | '150+'
  visitContext: string,    // 'solo' | 'couple' | 'family' | 'friends'
  photoIds: Id<'ugcPhotos'>[],
  helpfulCount: number,
  createdAt: number,
  updatedAt?: number,
  deletedAt?: number,      // Soft delete
}
```

## Edit History
Every edit records previous state:
```typescript
reviewEdits: {
  reviewId: Id<'reviews'>,
  editorUserId: Id<'users'>,
  prevText: string,
  nextText: string,
  editedAt: number,
}
```

## Soft Delete
Reviews are soft-deleted (retain for moderation/audit):
```typescript
export const deleteReview = mutation({
  args: { reviewId: v.id('reviews') },
  handler: async (ctx, { reviewId }) => {
    await ctx.db.patch(reviewId, { deletedAt: Date.now() });
    // Don't actually delete - keeps audit trail
  },
});
```

## Aggregate Updates
On review create/update/delete, update place aggregates:
- communityRatingAvg
- communityRatingCount

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] One review per user per place enforced
- [ ] Edit updates existing review
- [ ] Edit history recorded
- [ ] Soft delete working
- [ ] Aggregates updating correctly

## Task
Build community taste tags voting and the placeDishes aggregation for 'What to order' feature.

## Taste Tags System
Community can vote on tags for places:
- tagine, couscous, seafood, coffee, pastries, etc.
- Up/down voting per tag per place
- Anonymous allowed (with rate limits)

### placeTags Schema
```typescript
placeTags: defineTable({
  placeKey: v.string(),
  tag: v.string(),         // normalized key
  votesUp: v.number(),
  votesDown: v.number(),
  updatedAt: v.number(),
}).index('by_place', ['placeKey']),
```

### Voting Mutation
```typescript
export const voteTag = mutation({
  args: {
    placeKey: v.string(),
    tag: v.string(),
    vote: v.union(v.literal('up'), v.literal('down')),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, { placeKey, tag, vote }) => {
    // Rate limit check
    await checkRateLimit(ctx, 'tag_vote');

    const existing = await ctx.db
      .query('placeTags')
      .withIndex('by_place', (q) => q.eq('placeKey', placeKey))
      .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field('tag'), tag))
      .unique();

    if (existing) {
      const update = vote === 'up'
        ? { votesUp: existing.votesUp + 1 }
        : { votesDown: existing.votesDown + 1 };
      await ctx.db.patch(existing._id, { ...update, updatedAt: Date.now() });
    } else {
      await ctx.db.insert('placeTags', {
        placeKey,
        tag: normalizeTag(tag),
        votesUp: vote === 'up' ? 1 : 0,
        votesDown: vote === 'down' ? 1 : 0,
        updatedAt: Date.now(),
      });
    }
  },
});
```

## placeDishes Aggregation
Tracks which dishes are mentioned for each place.

Sources:
1. Review `dishesTried` fields
2. Curated card `mustTry` lists

### Schema
```typescript
placeDishes: defineTable({
  placeKey: v.string(),
  dish: v.string(),           // normalized, e.g. 'tagine'
  mentionsCount: v.number(),
  lastMentionedAt: v.number(),
  updatedAt: v.number(),
})
  .index('by_place', ['placeKey'])
  .index('by_dish', ['dish']),
```

### Aggregation Trigger
When review is created/updated:
```typescript
async function updateDishMentions(ctx, placeKey, dishes) {
  for (const dish of dishes) {
    const normalized = normalizeDish(dish);
    const existing = await findPlaceDish(ctx, placeKey, normalized);

    if (existing) {
      await ctx.db.patch(existing._id, {
        mentionsCount: existing.mentionsCount + 1,
        lastMentionedAt: Date.now(),
        updatedAt: Date.now(),
      });
    } else {
      await ctx.db.insert('placeDishes', {
        placeKey,
        dish: normalized,
        mentionsCount: 1,
        lastMentionedAt: Date.now(),
        updatedAt: Date.now(),
      });
    }
  }
}
```

## 'What to Order' Query
```typescript
export const getTopDishes = query({
  args: { placeKey: v.string() },
  handler: async (ctx, { placeKey }) => {
    const dishes = await ctx.db
      .query('placeDishes')
      .withIndex('by_place', (q) => q.eq('placeKey', placeKey))
      .collect();

    return dishes
      .sort((a, b) => b.mentionsCount - a.mentionsCount)
      .slice(0, 5);
  },
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Tag voting working
- [ ] Vote counts displaying
- [ ] Dish mentions aggregating from reviews
- [ ] 'What to order' showing top dishes

## Task
Implement optimistic updates for better perceived performance on user interactions.

## Actions to Optimize

### Favorite/Unfavorite
```typescript
const toggleFavorite = useMutation(api.lists.toggleFavorite)
  .withOptimisticUpdate((localStore, args) => {
    const place = localStore.getQuery(api.places.get, { id: args.placeId });
    if (place) {
      localStore.setQuery(api.places.get, { id: args.placeId }, {
        ...place,
        isFavorited: !place.isFavorited,
        favoritesCount: place.favoritesCount + (place.isFavorited ? -1 : 1),
      });
    }
  });
```

### Add to List
- Show item in list immediately
- Revert on error with toast

### Submit Review
- Show review with 'Posting...' indicator
- Update to confirmed state on success
- Remove and show error on failure

### Helpful Vote
- Increment count immediately
- Prevent double-voting client-side

### Tag Vote
- Update vote count immediately
- Debounce rapid voting

## Error Handling
```typescript
const mutation = useMutation(api.reviews.create)
  .withOptimisticUpdate((localStore, args) => {
    // Optimistic update...
  });

try {
  await mutation(args);
} catch (error) {
  // Convex automatically reverts optimistic update
  toast.error('Failed to save. Please try again.');
}
```

## UX Patterns
- Use subtle loading indicators (spinner in button)
- Don't block UI during mutation
- Show success confirmation briefly
- Clear error handling with retry option

## Testing
- Test network failure scenarios
- Test race conditions (rapid clicks)
- Verify rollback works correctly

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All specified actions have optimistic updates
- [ ] Rollback working on errors
- [ ] No UI jank during mutations
- [ ] Error feedback clear to users

## Task
Build the Dish Explorer - browse by dish + city to find top places for specific foods.

## Why This Differentiates
Google can tell you 'restaurants near me'. We can tell you 'where to get the best tagine in Gueliz' - because we have dish-level data from UGC.

## UI Flow
```
Home page → Dish quick-pick (e.g., 'Tagine')
    ↓
Dish Explorer page (/explore/dishes/tagine)
    ↓
Filter by city (optional)
    ↓
List of places ranked by dish-specific signals
```

## Ranking Algorithm
Uses ONLY owned signals:
```typescript
function calculateDishScore(place, dish) {
  const dishMentions = place.placeDishes[dish]?.mentionsCount || 0;
  const favorites = place.favoritesCount;
  const recentReviews = countRecentReviews(place, 30); // last 30 days

  return (
    (dishMentions * 3) +      // Dish mentions weighted highest
    (favorites * 1) +
    (recentReviews * 2)
  );
}
```

## Query
```typescript
export const exploreDish = query({
  args: {
    dish: v.string(),
    city: v.optional(v.string()),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, { dish, city }) => {
    // Get all places with this dish mentioned
    const dishMentions = await ctx.db
      .query('placeDishes')
      .withIndex('by_dish', (q) => q.eq('dish', normalizedDish(dish)))
      .collect();

    const placeKeys = dishMentions.map(d => d.placeKey);

    // Get place details + filter by city
    const places = await Promise.all(
      placeKeys.map(pk => getPlaceWithScore(ctx, pk, dish))
    );

    const filtered = city
      ? places.filter(p => p.city === city)
      : places;

    return filtered
      .sort((a, b) => b.dishScore - a.dishScore)
      .slice(0, 20);
  },
});
```

## Home Page Dish Quick-Picks
```typescript
const DISH_QUICK_PICKS = [
  { dish: 'tagine', label: 'Tagine', labelAr: 'طاجين' },
  { dish: 'couscous', label: 'Couscous', labelAr: 'كسكس' },
  { dish: 'pastilla', label: 'Pastilla', labelAr: 'بسطيلة' },
