## Task
Implement Google Places (New) search integration using session tokens for cost optimization.

## Session Token Flow
```
User starts typing
    ↓
Create session token
    ↓
Autocomplete calls (all use same token)
    ↓
User selects result
    ↓
Place Details call (same token)
    ↓
Session complete, token discarded
```

## Why Session Tokens
Google charges differently:
- Autocomplete without details: per-request pricing
- Autocomplete + details with token: bundled pricing

Using tokens can reduce costs significantly.

## Implementation
```typescript
// lib/searchSession.ts
class SearchSession {
  private token: string;
  private createdAt: number;
  private abortController: AbortController;

  constructor() {
    this.token = crypto.randomUUID();
    this.createdAt = Date.now();
    this.abortController = new AbortController();
  }

  async autocomplete(query: string): Promise<Prediction[]> {
    // Cancel previous in-flight request
    this.abortController.abort();
    this.abortController = new AbortController();

    return providerGateway.autocomplete({
      input: query,
      sessionToken: this.token,
      signal: this.abortController.signal,
    });
  }

  async selectPlace(placeId: string): Promise<PlaceDetails> {
    const details = await providerGateway.placeDetails({
      placeId,
      sessionToken: this.token,
    });

    // Session complete - token is consumed
    this.invalidate();
    return details;
  }
}
```

